# BikeGuru — Project Context

Indian bike research & comparison app. Budget ≤ ₹2.5L on-road. Prices always use **Bangalore, Karnataka** formula.

## Stack
- **Next.js 16** (App Router, Turbopack) + TypeScript strict
- **Supabase** — project ref `yqhssmriyfzfpaswomev` (ap-southeast-1)
- **OpenAI GPT-4o-mini** — chatbot + AI compare + scraper
- **Tailwind CSS v4** via `@import "tailwindcss"` — no tailwind.config.ts
- **lucide-react** for icons, **react-markdown + remark-gfm** for chat
- Fonts: `Bebas Neue` (headings, `var(--font-bebas)`) + `Space Grotesk` (body, `var(--font-space)`)

## Design System — Retro Bold
CSS variables in `app/globals.css`:
```
--cream: #F5F0E8      (page background)
--coral: #E8583D      (primary accent, CTAs)
--amber: #F5A623      (secondary accent, ratings)
--charcoal: #1A1A1A   (text, borders, headers)
--muted: #8B7355      (secondary text)
--border: #D4C5A9     (dividers)
```
Key utility classes: `.retro-border`, `.retro-btn`, `.retro-btn-coral`, `.card-hover`, `.tag-pill`, `.press-active`, `.slide-up`, `.skeleton`

Hard box-shadows (`3px 3px 0 var(--charcoal)`), no border-radius, uppercase tracking on labels.

## Pricing Rule — ALWAYS Bangalore Karnataka
```
road_tax = engine_cc <= 150 ? 13% : 14%
insurance = cc <= 150 ? ₹8,000 : cc <= 350 ? ₹12,000 : ₹15,000
handling = ₹3,500
on_road = ex_showroom + road_tax + insurance + handling
```
Never use Delhi/Mumbai prices. Always label as "Bangalore on-road".

## File Structure
```
app/
  page.tsx              — homepage (server component)
  bikes/page.tsx        — filterable listing (client, 2-col mobile grid)
  bikes/[id]/page.tsx   — detail page (server + BikeDetailClient)
  compare/page.tsx      — compare up to 3 bikes + AI analysis
  comparisons/page.tsx  — saved comparisons list
  wishlist/page.tsx     — saved bikes
  admin/page.tsx        — BikeWale scraper with autocomplete
  api/
    bikes/route.ts      — GET bikes with filters
    chat/route.ts       — OpenAI chatbot
    compare/route.ts    — POST save, GET all/one, DELETE comparison
    ai-compare/route.ts — GPT-4o-mini 8-dimension scoring
    scrape/route.ts     — BikeWale fetch + GPT extraction + Bangalore price
    wishlist/route.ts   — GET/POST/DELETE wishlist
components/
  bikes/BikeCard.tsx        — card with share button
  bikes/BikeImage.tsx       — img with error fallback
  bikes/BikeDetailClient.tsx — wishlist + compare + share (client)
  bikes/FilterPanel.tsx     — sidebar (desktop) / bottom sheet (mobile)
  bikes/AICompare.tsx       — AI analysis visual with score rings + bars
  chat/ChatBot.tsx          — floating chatbot with markdown rendering
  layout/Navbar.tsx         — sticky top nav
  layout/BottomNav.tsx      — mobile bottom nav (6 tabs)
  ui/ShareModal.tsx         — WhatsApp/X/copy/native share
lib/supabase.ts             — client + server supabase helpers
lib/utils.ts                — cn(), formatPrice(), formatPriceExact(), getSessionId()
types/bike.ts               — Bike interface + FilterState
```

## Supabase Tables
- `bikes` — all bike specs + image_url from imgd.aeplcdn.com CDN
- `wishlist` — session_id + bike_id
- `saved_comparisons` — id (short), name, bike_ids[], created_at
- `compare_list` — session_id + bike_id
- `chat_history` — session_id + role + content

## Mobile-First Rules
- Bottom nav fixed at bottom (`z-40`), 6 tabs, `md:hidden`
- Chat button: `bottom-20 md:bottom-6` to clear bottom nav
- Filters: bottom sheet on mobile (`slide-up`, `z-50`), sidebar on desktop
- Bike grid: `grid-cols-2` mobile, `xl:grid-cols-3` desktop
- Modals/pickers always use `z-[60]+` with backdrop to avoid greyout
- `press-active` class on all tappable elements
- Safe area: `paddingBottom: env(safe-area-inset-bottom)`

## Key Patterns
- Server components fetch from Supabase directly via `getServerSupabase()`
- Client components use `fetch('/api/...')`
- Images: plain `<img>` tags (not next/image) with `onError` fallback to 🏍️ emoji
- `getSessionId()` from `lib/utils.ts` for anonymous session tracking
- All commits by **Varshithvhegde** `<varshithvhegde@users.noreply.github.com>`

## BikeWale Image CDN Pattern
`https://imgd.aeplcdn.com/664x374/n/cw/ec/{NUMERIC_ID}/{slug}-right-side-view.jpeg`
Some bikes use `.png` extension. Verify URLs before saving.

## DO NOT
- Add `border-radius` anywhere — design is sharp/retro
- Use `next/image` for external CDN images (gets 403)
- Quote non-Bangalore on-road prices
- Add scooters (removed intentionally)
- Use `Twitter` icon from lucide-react (renamed — use `𝕏` text or XIcon)
